Matapato South MCA Hosea Toshi was involved in road accident on Friday when his car hit gazelles on Namanga road at 10.30am. His car rolled several times. Former Matapato North MCA Lesalaon Seki told the Star the ward rep was driving alone when gazelles “emerged from nowhere” at Olenkapapa borehole on the Bissil/Ng’atataek road.  The MCA was taken to Bissil dispensary for first aid and rushed to Kajiado referral hospital. Doctors recommended his evacuation to Nairobi Hospital.